										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Atletico Madrid are interested in signing Manchester City&#8217;s forward Alvaro Negredo. The Spanish giants are looking for a replacement for Diego Costa who will probably join Chelsea after the Brazil World Cup.</p>
<p>Atletico are willing to offer up to €31 millions for the Spanish international. Negredo had a good start at City but his performances decreased at the end of the season.</p>
<p>If the move will be done City will make a small some profit from the player sale as Negredo was brought for around €25 millions.</p>
<p>Negredo failed to make the squad for the World Cup but even so he remains one of the best Spanish strikers.</p>
<p>Atletico will have to reorganize quickly as David Villa will also leave the club.</p>
